INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2017-11-27 11:27:06','2017-11-27 11:27:06','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start writing!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world__trashed','','','2017-12-24 13:13:52','2017-12-24 13:13:52','',0,'http://flat.h1n.ru/tz/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(4,1,'2017-11-27 11:30:17','2017-11-27 11:30:17','','Movies','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2017-12-28 01:43:15','2017-12-28 01:43:15','',0,'http://flat.h1n.ru/tz/?page_id=4',0,'page','',0),(5,1,'2017-11-27 11:30:17','2017-11-27 11:30:17','qweqwe','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-11-27 11:30:17','2017-11-27 11:30:17','',4,'http://flat.h1n.ru/tz/2017/11/27/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2017-11-27 11:30:32','2017-11-27 11:30:32','qweqwe','Test','','inherit','closed','closed','','4-revision-v1','','','2017-11-27 11:30:32','2017-11-27 11:30:32','',4,'http://flat.h1n.ru/tz/2017/11/27/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(7,1,'2017-11-27 12:58:26','2017-11-27 12:58:26','The story begins inÂ <a title=\"Shire (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shire_(Middle-earth)\">the Shire</a>, where the hobbitÂ <a title=\"Frodo Baggins\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frodo_Baggins\">Frodo Baggins</a>Â inheritsÂ <a title=\"One Ring\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/One_Ring\">the Ring</a>Â fromÂ <a title=\"Bilbo Baggins\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilbo_Baggins\">Bilbo Baggins</a>, his cousin<sup id=\"cite_ref-cousins_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Lord_of_the_Rings#cite_note-cousins-15\">[note 3]</a></sup>Â and guardian. Neither hobbit is aware of the Ring\'s nature, butÂ <a title=\"Gandalf\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gandalf\">Gandalf the Grey</a>, aÂ <a title=\"Wizard (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wizard_(Middle-earth)\">wizard</a>Â and an old friend of Bilbo, suspects it to be Sauron\'s Ring. Many years later, after Gandalf confirms his guess, he tells Frodo the history of the Ring and counsels him to take it away from the Shire. Frodo sets out, accompanied by his gardener and friend,Â <a title=\"Samwise Gamgee\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Samwise_Gamgee\">Samwise (\"Sam\") Gamgee</a>, and two cousins,Â <a title=\"Meriadoc Brandybuck\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\">Meriadoc Brandybuck</a>, called Merry, andÂ <a title=\"Peregrin Took\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\">Peregrin Took</a>, called Pippin. They are nearly caught by theÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Black Riders\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Riders\">Black Riders</a>Â but shake off their pursuers by cutting through theÂ <a title=\"Old Forest\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Old_Forest\">Old Forest</a>. There they are aided byÂ <a title=\"Tom Bombadil\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tom_Bombadil\">Tom Bombadil</a>, a strange and merry fellow who lives with his wifeÂ <a title=\"Goldberry\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Goldberry\">Goldberry</a>Â in the forest.\r\n\r\nThe Hobbits reach the town ofÂ <a title=\"Bree (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bree_(Middle-earth)\">Bree</a>, where they encounter aÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ranger of the North\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranger_of_the_North\">Ranger</a>Â namedÂ <a title=\"Aragorn\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\">Strider</a>, whom Gandalf had mentioned in a letter. Strider persuades the hobbits to take him on as their guide and protector. Together, they leave Bree after another close escape from the Black Riders. On the hill ofÂ <a title=\"Weathertop\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weathertop\">Weathertop</a>, they are again attacked by the Black Riders, who wound Frodo with a cursed blade. Strider fights them off with fire and leads the hobbits towards theÂ <a title=\"Elf (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\">Elven</a>Â refuge ofÂ <a title=\"Rivendell\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rivendell\">Rivendell</a>. Frodo falls deathly sick from the wound. The Black Riders nearly overtake Frodo at the Ford ofÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bruinen\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bruinen\">Bruinen</a>, but flood waters summoned byÂ <a title=\"Elrond\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elrond\">Elrond</a>, master of Rivendell, rise up and overwhelm them.\r\n\r\nFrodo recovers in Rivendell under Elrond\'s care. The Council of Elrond discusses the history of Sauron and the Ring. Strider is revealed to beÂ <a title=\"Aragorn\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\">Aragorn</a>, Isildur\'s heir. Gandalf reports that Sauron has corruptedÂ <a title=\"Saruman\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\">Saruman</a>, chief of the wizards. The Council decides that the Ring must be destroyed, but that can only be done by sending it to the Fire ofÂ <a title=\"Mount Doom\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Doom\">Mount Doom</a>Â in Mordor, where it was forged. Frodo takes this task upon himself. Elrond, with the advice of Gandalf, chooses companions for him. TheÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fellowship of the Ring (characters)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fellowship_of_the_Ring_(characters)\">Company of the Ring</a>Â are nine in number: Frodo, Sam, Merry, Pippin, Aragorn, Gandalf,Â <a title=\"Gimli (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\">Gimli</a>Â theÂ <a title=\"Dwarf (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dwarf_(Middle-earth)\">Dwarf</a>,Â <a title=\"Legolas\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legolas\">Legolas</a>theÂ <a title=\"Elf (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Elf_(Middle-earth)\">Elf</a>, and the ManÂ <a title=\"Boromir\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\">Boromir</a>, son of theÂ <a title=\"Stewards of Gondor\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stewards_of_Gondor\">Ruling Steward</a>Â <a title=\"Denethor\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Denethor\">Denethor</a>Â of the land ofÂ <a title=\"Gondor\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gondor\">Gondor</a>.\r\n\r\nAfter a failed attempt to cross theÂ <a title=\"Misty Mountains\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Misty_Mountains\">Misty Mountains</a>Â through the Redhorn Pass, the Company are forced to take a perilous path through theÂ <a title=\"Moria (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moria_(Middle-earth)\">Mines of Moria</a>. They are attacked by theÂ <a title=\"Watcher in the Water\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Watcher_in_the_Water\">Watcher in the Water</a>before the doors of Moria. Inside Moria, they learn of the fate ofÂ <a title=\"Balin (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balin_(Middle-earth)\">Balin</a>Â and his colony of Dwarves. After surviving an attack, they are pursued byÂ <a title=\"Orc (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\">Orcs</a>Â and by an ancient demon called aÂ <a title=\"Balrog\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Balrog\">Balrog</a>. Gandalf faces the Balrog, and both of them fall into the abyss. The others escape and find refuge in the Elven forest ofÂ <a title=\"LothlÃ³rien\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lothl%C3%B3rien\">LothlÃ³rien</a>, where they are counselled byÂ <a title=\"Galadriel\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Galadriel\">Galadriel</a>Â andÂ <a title=\"Celeborn\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Celeborn\">Celeborn</a>.\r\n\r\nWith boats and gifts from Galadriel, the Company travel down the RiverÂ <a title=\"Anduin\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anduin\">Anduin</a>Â to the hill ofÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Amon Hen\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amon_Hen\">Amon Hen</a>. There, Boromir tries to take the Ring from Frodo, but Frodo puts it on and disappears. After the Company scatters to search for Frodo, they are attacked by Orcs. Frodo chooses to go alone to Mordor, but Sam guesses what he intends and goes with him.','The Lord Of The Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring','','publish','closed','closed','','the-lord-of-the-rings-the-fellowship-of-the-ring','','','2017-11-29 18:24:14','2017-11-29 18:24:14','',0,'http://flat.h1n.ru/tz/?post_type=movie&#038;p=7',0,'movie','',0),(8,1,'2017-11-27 13:01:42','2017-11-27 13:01:42','<a title=\"Orc (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orc_(Middle-earth)\">Orcs</a>Â sent byÂ <a title=\"Saruman\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saruman\">Saruman</a>Â andÂ <a title=\"Sauron\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sauron\">Sauron</a>Â killÂ <a title=\"Boromir\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boromir\">Boromir</a>Â and takeÂ <a title=\"Meriadoc Brandybuck\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meriadoc_Brandybuck\">Merry</a>Â andÂ <a title=\"Peregrin Took\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peregrin_Took\">Pippin</a>.Â <a title=\"Aragorn\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aragorn\">Aragorn</a>,Â <a title=\"Gimli (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gimli_(Middle-earth)\">Gimli</a>Â andÂ <a title=\"Legolas\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Legolas\">Legolas</a>Â debate amongst themselves which pair ofÂ <a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hobbits\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hobbits\">hobbits</a>Â to follow. They decide to pursue the Orcs bearing Merry and Pippin to Saruman. In the kingdom ofÂ <a title=\"Rohan (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)\">Rohan</a>, the Orcs are slain by a company of theÂ <a title=\"Rohan (Middle-earth)\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rohan_(Middle-earth)#People\">Rohirrim</a>. Merry and Pippin escape intoÂ <a title=\"Fangorn\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fangorn\">Fangorn</a>Â Forest, where they are befrie